review_blob: Lightly sour and very sweet with a tinge of apple. The overall feel of #6 is one slightly less sticky than some meads with a nice palate. A pleasant dessert drink but less so for meals or digestifs.

With its mild and fresh demeanor this one sits well with a day in the sun. Much more than that, unfortunately, it cannot deliver on. There are sweet notes of citrus and traces of something not quite unlike elderflower but they stay only shortly and leaves a pleasantly quenched thirst but little else. The bitterness of the myrica doesnt really present itself.
